            <a><a/><p><font color="yellow">Because Mars’s atmosphere is 100 times thinner than ours, their air pressure Is also low – as little as 1/1000th of that of Earth. For comparison, the pressure on Mt. Everest is 1/3rd that at sea level.  There is so little pressure on Mars that there is not enough to prevent water from exploding from below the surface and boiling away, nor enough to keep your body’s fluids from boiling as well.  Perhaps less damaging but still daunting would be that the water in your lungs, tears and saliva would evaporate immediately.</font></p>
			
			
			
