                <p><font color="yellow">Long-term survival would require thickening the atmosphere of Mars, increasing the pressure in order to keep the heat from escaping and water – including our bodily fluids – from boiling.  Margarita Marinova has suggested that we might be able to do this by using PFC’s (perflourocarbons) – essentially creating a greenhouse effect on Mars – exactly what we have done – to our detriment – on Earth.</font></p>
                  
            <p><font color="yellow">Other suggestions on increasing the atmospheric pressure on Mars have been to launch a satellite that would point a giant mirror on its polar ice caps, converting the CO2 to a gas.  Or using solar panels to convert the CO2 to carbon and oxygen.</font></p>
			
			
